#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn12.53"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.53:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.53:0.2"
msgid "6. Dukkhavagga "
msgstr "6. Suffering "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.53:0.3"
msgid "53. Saṃyojanasutta "
msgstr "53. Fetters "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.86, sc1
msgctxt "sn12.53:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.53:1.2"
msgid "“Saṃyojaniyesu, bhikkhave, dhammesu assādānupassino viharato taṇhā pavaḍḍhati. "
msgstr "“There are things that are prone to being fettered. When you concentrate on the gratification provided by these things, your craving grows. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.3"
msgid "Taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ; "
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.4"
msgid "upādānapaccayā bhavo; "
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.5"
msgid "bhavapaccayā jāti; "
msgstr "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.6"
msgid "jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. "
msgstr "Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.7"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn12.53:2.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, telañca paṭicca vaṭṭiñca paṭicca telappadīpo jhāyeyya. "
msgstr "Suppose an oil lamp depended on oil and a wick to burn. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.2"
msgid "Tatra puriso kālena kālaṃ telaṃ āsiñceyya vaṭṭiṃ upasaṃhareyya. "
msgstr "And from time to time someone would pour oil in and adjust the wick. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.3"
msgid "Evañhi so, bhikkhave, telappadīpo tadāhāro tadupādāno ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ jaleyya. "
msgstr "Fueled and sustained by that, the oil lamp would burn for a long time. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.53:2.4"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyesu dhammesu assādānupassino viharato taṇhā pavaḍḍhati. "
msgstr "In the same way, there are things that are prone to being fettered. When you concentrate on the gratification provided by these things, your craving grows. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.5"
msgid "Taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ; "
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.6"
msgid "upādānapaccayā bhavo; "
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.7"
msgid "bhavapaccayā jāti; "
msgstr "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.8"
msgid "jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. "
msgstr "Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.9"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn12.53:3.1"
msgid "Saṃyojaniyesu, bhikkhave, dhammesu ādīnavānupassino viharato taṇhā nirujjhati. "
msgstr "There are things that are prone to being fettered. When you concentrate on the drawbacks of these things, your craving ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:3.2"
msgid "Taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho; "
msgstr "When craving ceases, grasping ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:3.3"
msgid "upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho; "
msgstr "When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:3.4"
msgid "bhavanirodhā jātinirodho; "
msgstr "When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:3.5"
msgid "jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:3.6"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn12.53:4.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, telañca paṭicca vaṭṭiñca paṭicca telappadīpo jhāyeyya. "
msgstr "Suppose an oil lamp depended on oil and a wick to burn. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:4.2"
msgid "Tatra puriso na kālena kālaṃ telaṃ āsiñceyya na vaṭṭiṃ upasaṃhareyya. "
msgstr "And no-one would pour oil in and adjust the wick from time to time. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:4.3"
msgid "Evañhi so, bhikkhave, telappadīpo purimassa ca upādānassa pariyādānā aññassa ca anupahārā anāhāro nibbāyeyya. "
msgstr "As the original fuel is used up and no more is added, the oil lamp would be extinguished due to lack of fuel. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.53:4.4"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyesu dhammesu ādīnavānupassino viharato taṇhā nirujjhati. "
msgstr "In the same way, there are things that are prone to being fettered. When you concentrate on the drawbacks of these things, your craving ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.53:4.5"
msgid "Taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho … pe … "
msgstr "When craving ceases, grasping ceases. … "

msgctxt "sn12.53:4.6"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.53:4.7"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

